  <summary date="2019-06-26T19:10:22Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Shareholder Protection Act of 2019

This bill requires shareholder authorization of certain political expenditures by an issuer. A violation of this requirement shall be considered&#160;a breach of fiduciary duty, and the officers and directors who authorized the expenditure shall be subject to joint and several liability. An issuer must require a board vote with respect to political expenditures in excess of $50,000 and, within 48 hours, make publicly available the individual votes of each board member.</summary>
